        "ContentTypeId": "0x0110002675B935B1E1CA40903215A1EC22F4C4",
        "Title": "LAFPoint Training Every Tuesday in September",
        "Body": "<div class=\"ExternalClass580EC61B21284EF59DD878FA848D952C\"><h4><span><b>Training sessions for LAFPoint are every Tuesday in September.</b></span><span><b>&#160;&#160;</b></span></h4><p><span>Each training session runs from 2&#58;00 – 3&#58;00 p.m. in room 1078. Please email Beverly Palmer to sign up for one of the sessions onSeptember 8, 15, 22 or 29. Space is limited, so sign up soon! </span></p><p><span>&#160;</span><b style=\"color&#58;inherit;\">A big shout out to all who attended the first training yesterday.&#160;</b></p><p><span>Thanks for being pioneers! Pleasecontinue exploring and using LAFPoint every day. If you spend a few minutesclicking around each day, you’ll become an LAFPoint pro before you know it.Remember that because we host LAFPoint on our own servers, you need to belogged in to the network at your desk or through remote access to get toLAFPoint. Just open a browser (Chrome or Firefox are recommended) at your deskor through remote access and go to </span><a href=\"/\"><span>https&#58;//lafpoint.lafchicago.org</span></a><span> to log in with your LAF credentials. Soonwe will set up LAFPoint so that it opens automatically when you log in, justlike SharePoint 2010 does now. </span></p><h4><span><b>September is Migration Month at LAF.&#160;</b></span></h4><p><span>Once you have attended a Tuesday Training session, you should start migrating files from your individual staff folder on the G&#58; Drive to your OneDrive on LAFPoint. The sooner you can do this, the better. Remember that the G&#58; Drive becomes“read only” on October 6, so we will need to save everything to LAFPoint after October 6.</span></p><p><span></span></p></div>",
