        "Title": "What's the point of SharePoint?  Social computing.",
        "Body": "<div class=\"ExternalClass5EB803BF962E4501AFD8ED35A55F17E6\"><p>​Social computing is the concept behind many of the features on SharePoint, including blogs, communities (discussion groups), news feeds, site feeds, RSS, team and project sites, and wikis.&#160; The premise is that&#160;these&#160;features create additional ways to collaborate and communicate and, importantly,  better ways to store knowledge than email and a file share (the G Drive).&#160; Go <a href=\"https&#58;//technet.microsoft.com/en-us/library/ee662531.aspx\">here</a> for Microsoft's explanation of social computing.<br></p></div>",
