        "Title": "Join the People with Disabilities Task Force in Events Celebrating 25 years of the ADA",
        "Body": "<div class=\"ExternalClass8C92085DF9E64E4B9C295A891FF34F9C\"><p>This year marks 25 years since the Americans with Disabilities Act became law, and a group of disability related organizations in Chicago created ADA 25 Chicago to commemorate the anniversary. &#160;They are organizing educational and cultural activities to celebrate and learn about a variety of issues related to people with disabilities and the history of the ADA.<br><br>The full calendar of events is <a href=\"http&#58;//ada25chicago.org/calendar/\">here</a>.<br><br>At least one member of the People with Disabilities Task Force will be at the following events&#58;<br><br><a href=\"http&#58;//ada25chicago.org/calendar/communication-accessibility-planning-ahead-for-events-and-programs/\" style=\"background-color&#58;rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Communication Accessibility&#58; Planning Ahead for Events and Programs</a><br><span>Donors Forum (208 S LaSalle, Suite 1540), October 26, 9-11 AM&#160;<br></span><br><a href=\"http&#58;//ada25chicago.org/calendar/behavioral-memory-and-cognitive-disability-accommodations/\" style=\"background-color&#58;rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Behavioral, Memory and Cognitive Disability Accommodations</a><br><span>Donors Forum (208 S LaSalle, Suite 1540), November 9, 9-11 AM<br></span><span><br>Space is limited. &#160;You can register through the links above. &#160;Contact Kim Cramer if you're interested in either of these events and would like to meet and walk over together!&#160;</span></p></div>",
