        "Title": "LAFPoint Update",
        "Body": "<div class=\"ExternalClass072B97B6FBBB492495144941D668408B\"><p><b><span style=\"color&#58;#1f497d;\">Training&#58;</span></b><span style=\"color&#58;rgb(31, 73, 125);\"> We had our first LAFPoint Q&amp;A session last week. This was an informal session (no laptops) for people to ask any questions they wanted to ask about LAFPoint. Thanks to all who attended last week and asked excellent questions! We have two more LAFPoint Q&amp;A sessions this month, on October 15 and 29. Check out the Training Events on LAFPoint for details and look for more information on Q&amp;A sessions and other training coming in November.</span><br></p><p><span style=\"color&#58;#212121;\"></span></p><p><b><span style=\"color&#58;#1f497d;\">LAFPointDevelopment&#58;</span></b><span style=\"color&#58;rgb(31, 73, 125);\"> Parts of LAFPoint are still under construction. The Work Group Documents are a top priority, and we’re also tweaking things here and there based on feedback from staff. We’ll be developing more sections of LAFPoint in the coming weeks and months.</span></p><p><span style=\"color&#58;#212121;\"></span></p><p><b><span style=\"color&#58;#1f497d;\">October is Migration Month.</span></b><span style=\"color&#58;rgb(31, 73, 125);\"> Now that we’re all using LAFPoint, we need to migrate content from SharePoint 2010 to LAFPoint and from the G&#58; Drive to LAFPoint as soon as practical. The IT staff are working on the migration of content from SP 2010 and the Curators are working on the migration of content from the G&#58;Drive.</span></p><p><span style=\"color&#58;#212121;\"></span></p><p><span style=\"color&#58;#1f497d;\">Questions,compliments, concerns? Feel free to post them on the LAFPoint Discussion Board or email the LAFPoint Curators at &#160;&lt;<span style=\"color&#58;#1f497d;\"><a href=\"mailto&#58;LAFPointCurators@lafchicago.org\">LAFPointCurators@lafchicago.or</a>g&gt;.&#160;</span></span><span style=\"color&#58;#212121;\"></span></p></div>",
