        "Title": "Making Connections",
        "Body": "<div class=\"ExternalClass2271B01CA6D84D09BDC5650BFE6D9197\"><p><span style=\"color&#58;black;\">Mrs. Harris came to see Shirley Wilkins at the Garfield Community Center, one of LAF’s Public Benefits Enrollment Sites.<span>&#160; </span>While completing her application for SNAP and medical benefits, Shirley learned that Mrs. Harris had traveled from St. Louis, MO, fleeing an abusive relationship.<span>&#160;&#160;</span>Mrs. Harris had been with her abuser since age 14 and now, at the age of 53,&#160;suffers from mental illness.<span>&#160; </span>She arrived in Chicago homeless, and un-medicated.<span>&#160; </span>Shirley introduced her to one of the DV team members at the Garfield office. As a result of that connection, Mrs. Harris was given a cell phone in order to communicate, is allowed to pick up her mail there in order to receive notices from&#160;social security, and was referred to the Bobby Wright Clinic where she&#160;gets her prescription medication. And, now Mrs. Harris receives SNAP&#160;and a medical card. She is currently on the waiting list for&#160;Bobby Wright Housing.<span>&#160; </span>Thanks to people working in the community, like Shirley Wilkins, Mrs. Harris has gone from a 39 year abusive relationship, to becoming a self-sufficient person living in peace.&#160;</span></p><p><font color=\"#000000\" face=\"Calibri\">This message is brought to you by the DV Task Force, in recognition of DV Awareness Month.&#160; </font><br></p></div>",
