        "Title": "Celebrating volunteers- Al Cichon",
        "Body": "<div class=\"ExternalClassDF93EB3008AA4E9FB84CDB3B2202953B\"><title>Current Selection</title><p>&#160; Al Cichon has been volunteering with LAF since 2015, but he’s led a lifetime of service.&#160; Throughout his thirty year career in banking, Al always found time to give back to the community by mentoring, providing financial literacy, and teaching courses on banking as an adjunct professor at Harper College.&#160; When he retired, Al wanted to find a way to keep serving the community so he reached out to an old friend. </p><p>Before starting his career as a banker, Al worked as a teacher and principal at St. Boniface.&#160; While he was the principal, Al hired LAF’s very own Rich Cozzola to teach 6th grade, and they’ve been great friends ever since.&#160; Al knew all about LAF through Rich, so after retiring we were his first choice for volunteering. </p><p>Although he was hesitant at first, working at a law firm, Al found that everyone at LAF was welcoming, open to collaboration, and very passionate about the work they do.&#160; Al comes in once a week to do file organization and digitizing of old paperwork.&#160; In his three years, Al has worked on projects for Rich Cozzola, Kate Shank, and Kate McCartin.&#160; Its tasks like these that often get overlooked, but are pivotal in keeping everything moving smoothly.&#160; Through his work, Al is helping LAF move into the digital age. </p><p>When he’s not scanning documents or telling quips about Chicago through the years, Al can be found riding his bike on the Lakefront Trail or spending quality time with his wife, two daughters, and their four grandchildren.&#160; Also, if you’re ever looking to get out of the office and go on a guided tour of downtown, Al is your guy. </p><p>Thank you for taking some time away from your busy schedule to volunteer at LAF.&#160; Your stories are always welcome and we’re lucky to have you. </p></div>",
