        "Title": "Heaston Victory",
        "Body": "<div class=\"ExternalClass710F7384345E47418C7F4ACC50860950\"><p>Rachel Heaston's client had only been married for 6 years. By statute, the client was&#160;entitled to maintenance for&#160;1.2 years, and Rachel had already gotten the client&#160;maintenance for 2 years&#160;at $500 per month.&#160; So, it seemed rather hopeless when the husband asked for&#160;maintenance to terminate.&#160; During those 2 years, however, Rachel's client began collecting disability benefits and it was clear that she could not re-enter the workforce.&#160; After Rachel told this sad tale to the judge,&#160;and gave it the Heaston-spin, the judge wiped his eyes and increased the maintenance payments to $608 for an additional 2.8 years. Way to go, Rachel!&#160; &#160;&#160;&#160; <br></p></div>",
