        "Body": "<div class=\"ExternalClass111F15A2B2BC4DC8A1B6D13C139573CB\"><p>&lt;![endif]--&gt;</p><h3><span style=\"color&#58;#3d3d3d;\"><a href=\"http&#58;//salsa3.salsalabs.com/dia/track.jsp?v=2&amp;c=nbqH0hMhU5JagEb63AUcxibwQoPCmr28\">Take5&#58; More charter news, inflated grad rates, faster Internet in schools</a></span></h3><span style=\"color&#58;#3d3d3d;\">A half-dozen legalaid organizations want CPS to take co-locations of neighborhood schools withcharter schools off the table this year. Meanwhile, the graduation rate at CityColleges is under scrutiny, as are cushy severance packages from the IllinoisState Board of Education.</span><p></p></div>",
