        "ContentTypeId": "0x0110002675B935B1E1CA40903215A1EC22F4C4",
        "Title": "Celebrating Volunteers - Howard Goffen",
        "Body": "<div class=\"ExternalClassB3B5F22A5398412BA78F4DDE99DDE56C\"><p style=\"color&#58;rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><span>Howard Goffen began volunteering at LAF in 2004. Before joining us, he spent 20 years working as a trial lawyer at Jesmer &amp; Harris representing taxi and limo drivers. &#160;While attending a post-retirement seminar put on by the Chicago Bar Foundation, he saw a presentation by Bill Kolen and John Held about volunteering at LAF. He thought it was a good idea, so he reached out to his friend, Dick Hess, and inquired about volunteering.</span><br></p><p style=\"color&#58;rgb(0, 0, 0);\">He originally wanted to be at the Evanston office, because it was close to home, but he was placed at the NW office. &#160;Howard spent the next 7 1/2 years working at this office doing a variety of cases in all different practice areas. &#160;Coming from a structured firm, with 20 attorneys, administrative staff, and paralegals, he was amazed at the work our attorneys did, and a bit perplexed by the laid back atmosphere sometimes. &#160;When we moved into our downtown office he said it felt like he had died and gone to heaven.</p><p style=\"color&#58;rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Last December, Howard was thinking about hanging up the legal aid gloves for good, but Michelle Weinberg convinced him to stick around. &#160;Howard's work doing simple wills and Powers of Attorney was an area of need for our organization, and thankfully he agreed to continue doing these.</p><p style=\"color&#58;rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><span>Thanks to Michelle for convincing him to stay, and thank you to Howard for all the work you do.</span></p><p style=\"color&#58;rgb(0, 0, 0);\">One last note,&#160;<span>In 2012, Howard won the ABA Pro Bono Publico Award which is presented each year by the Standing Committee on Pro Bono and Public Service to honor individual lawyers, law firms, law schools, government attorney offices, corporate law departments and other institutions in the legal profession that have enhanced the human dignity of others by improving or delivering volunteer legal services to the poor.</span></p><p style=\"color&#58;rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><a>http&#58;//www.americanbar.org/content/dam/aba/administrative/probono_public_service/ls_pb_pbp_2012_goffen.mov</a></p></div>",
