        "ContentTypeId": "0x0110002675B935B1E1CA40903215A1EC22F4C4",
        "Title": "What's Coming Soon in LAFPoint",
        "Body": "<div class=\"ExternalClass68E82876604F4DC0B0176321FE794E47\"><p>Our SharePoint consultant, Mark Pace, was here at LAF earlier this week to meet with our IT staff, individual users, our Core Group and others. Here's a smattering of what is coming to LAFPoint in the next few weeks&#58;&#160;</p><p>- Work Group Sub-Sites that will have the same functionality as the MySites so that each work group can set up their own folders, blog posts, newsfeeds, etc;&#160;</p><p>- Comments to Blog Posts;&#160;</p><p>- Easier access to the full Microsoft applications such as Word, Excel, etc., so that users can get to the full applications faster if they really don't want to use the Web Apps - but the Web Apps are agile and quick so be sure to give them a try;&#160;</p><p>- Better visual design with a layout that is easier on the eyes and includes more color;&#160;</p><p>- And more!&#160;</p><p>Please keep sharing comments and questions with individual Curators, the Curators group at <a href=\"mailto&#58;LAFPointCurators@lafchicago.org\">LAFPointCurators@lafchicago.org​</a>&#160;or on the LAFPoint Discussion Board, and be sure to keep an eye on the Training Calendar for more LAFPoint training events and Q&amp;A sessions in November.&#160;</p><p><br></p></div>",
