        "Title": "Rachel Zemke Brightens Up Client's Life",
        "Body": "<div class=\"ExternalClass398B64370C2646D0A018B01F38098A6A\"><p><font face=\"Calibri\"><font size=\"3\"><font color=\"#000000\">Ms. Albar is an&#160;81 year old disabled woman who lives withone of her daughters, Helena. <span>&#160;</span></font></font><font color=\"#000000\" size=\"3\">Ms. Albarhas been estranged from her husband for ten years, although they are notlegally divorced.</font><span><font color=\"#000000\" size=\"3\">&#160; </font></span><font color=\"#000000\" size=\"3\">In July, Ms. Albar andHelena were shocked to receive a $2,934.46 electric bill.</font><span><font color=\"#000000\" size=\"3\">&#160; </font></span><font color=\"#000000\" size=\"3\">Without warning, Commonwealth Edison </font><span><font color=\"#000000\" size=\"3\">&#160;</font></span><font color=\"#000000\" size=\"3\">had </font><span><font color=\"#000000\" size=\"3\">&#160;</font></span><font color=\"#000000\" size=\"3\">“transferred” this large amount from Ms. Albar’sestranged husband’s name to her account</font><span><font color=\"#000000\" size=\"3\">&#160;</font></span><font color=\"#000000\" size=\"3\">--</font><span><font color=\"#000000\" size=\"3\">&#160; </font></span><font color=\"#000000\" size=\"3\">the bill apparently was incurred by another daughter, Aviva, after Mr. Albar gave permission to use his name to obtain service at her residence. </font><span><font color=\"#000000\" size=\"3\">&#160;</font></span><font color=\"#000000\" size=\"3\">Unbeknownst to Ms. Albar, her estranged husband’s name was somehow still connected to her account!&#160;</font><font size=\"3\"><font color=\"#000000\"><span>&#160;</span></font></font></font></p><p><font face=\"Calibri\"><font size=\"3\"><font color=\"#000000\">When she called us, Commonwealth Edison had already shut off the electric service, but with help from LAF Intern Rachel Zemke, Helena was able to work with her mother’s doctor to get a medical letter in to the company and the lights were turned back on, temporarily.<span>&#160; </span></font></font><font size=\"3\"><font color=\"#000000\">This did not eliminate the outrageous bill, however. </font></font></font></p><p><font face=\"Calibri\"><font size=\"3\"><font color=\"#000000\">With the client on the phone, LAF attempted to make an official complaint to the Illinois Commerce Commission about the situation.<span>&#160; </span></font></font><font size=\"3\"><font color=\"#000000\">However, the ICC consumer advocate told Ms. Albar and Rachel that since the client and her husband were still legally married, it was legally Ms. Albar’s debt and she could not raise any issue of identity theft.The advocate refused to log the call as an “informal complaint,” a necessary designation to get ComEd to address the issue. After conferring with supervisor Michelle Weinberg, Rachel got back on the phone with the ICC and demanded that they log this case as an informal complaint because Ms. Akbar has been estranged from her husband for over 10 years and she did not benefit in any way from the electric service. The consumer advocate reluctantly agreed to do so&#160;&#160; and then hung up on Rachel and the client. </font></font></font></p><p><font color=\"#000000\" face=\"Times New Roman\" size=\"3\"></font><font face=\"Calibri\"><font size=\"3\"><font color=\"#000000\">Persistence paid off.<span>&#160;</span></font></font><font color=\"#000000\" size=\"3\">ComEd contacted LAF and Ms. Albar for a telephone conference to discussthe issue.</font><span><font color=\"#000000\" size=\"3\">&#160; </font></span><font size=\"3\"><font color=\"#000000\">Upon Rachel's tenacious advocacy, the company agreed to delete the balance from Ms. Akbar’s account, permanently remove her husband’s name from the account, and even agreed to waive some late fees that Ms. Akbar had not paid during the dispute. Ms. Akbar and her daughter are now back to paying just their own electric bill, and they are safe from having to face this situation again!</font></font></font></p><p><font color=\"#000000\" face=\"Times New Roman\" size=\"3\"></font></p></div>",
