        "Title": "CIVIL RIGHTS  VICTORY",
        "Body": "<div class=\"ExternalClassA0DE8AA8C65B49C280F58A3941ACF0F0\"><p><br>Sometimes things get lost in the shuffle. Did you know LAF won an important Section 504 Complaint in the Office of Civil Rights of the U.S. Department of Education.&#160; </p><p>Verity Sandell was lead, Kate Gladson co-counseled. &#160;Case decided in February had individual and policy implications for CPS. Here is the handy link on LAFPoint. Read it and congratulate them on their great work.</p><p><font color=\"#646464\"><a href=\"https&#58;//my.lafpoint.lafchicago.org/personal/zlang/Ed%20Law%20DCFS%20Project/_layouts/15/WopiFrame.aspx?sourcedoc=/personal/zlang/Ed%20Law%20DCFS%20Project/Shared%20Documents/Education%20Open%20Cases/Walton%2c%20Jeremiah%20-%20I/OCR%20Documents/2-13-2015%20Concept%20Complainant%20Letter.pdf&amp;action=default\">https&#58;//my.lafpoint.lafchicago.org/personal/zlang/Ed%20Law%20DCFS%20Project/_layouts/15/WopiFrame.aspx?sourcedoc=/personal/zlang/Ed%20Law%20DCFS%20Project/Shared%20Documents/Education%20Open%20Cases/Walton,%20Jeremiah%20-%20I/OCR%20Documents/2-13-2015%20Concept%20Complainant%20Letter.pdf&amp;action=default</a></font></p></div>",
