        "ContentTypeId": "0x0110002675B935B1E1CA40903215A1EC22F4C4",
        "Title": "Lizzie & Eli \"are the champions.\"",
        "Body": "<div class=\"ExternalClass9F18ECB8254C41488204BEEB4B96AFD1\"><p><font color=\"#000000\" face=\"Times New Roman\" size=\"3\"></font><font size=\"3\"><font color=\"#000000\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">Michael Kidd was facing eviction from a public housing development in suburban Cook County because (1) he legally possessed a gun on the property in violation of HACC’s blanket ban against guns, a ban that likely violates the Second Amendment, (2) he got into arguments with a belligerent neighbor who has since been evicted and barred from the development, and (3) he allegedly threatened the property manager after she issued him a written warning for getting into an argument he did not start.</font></font></font></p><p><font color=\"#000000\" face=\"Times New Roman\" size=\"3\"></font><font face=\"Times New Roman\"><font size=\"3\"><font color=\"#000000\">Lizzie Rosenthal and Eli Wade-Scott defended Mr. Kidd because he posed no threat to anyone.<span>&#160; </span></font></font><font color=\"#000000\" size=\"3\">He is a licensed security guard who possessed the gun because he needed it for work, and he eventually got rid of the gun because he needed his subsidized tenancy more than his job.</font><span><font color=\"#000000\" size=\"3\">&#160; </font></span><font color=\"#000000\" size=\"3\">Furthermore, he did not start the arguments with his neighbor, and he never threatened the property manager.</font><span><font color=\"#000000\" size=\"3\">&#160; </font></span><font color=\"#000000\" size=\"3\">He just expressed his frustration with her decision to hold him responsible for altercations he did not start.</font><span><font color=\"#000000\" size=\"3\">&#160; </font></span><font size=\"3\"><font color=\"#000000\">We also had strong waiver arguments, even though the court erred by denying our dispositive motion&#160;based on these arguments.</font></font></font></p><p><font color=\"#000000\" face=\"Times New Roman\" size=\"3\"></font><font face=\"Times New Roman\"><font size=\"3\"><font color=\"#000000\">This week the case went to trial before a jury.<span>&#160; </span></font></font><font size=\"3\"><font color=\"#000000\">There were many twists and turns – too many to describe in this posting – but here are a few highlights&#58; Lizzie and Eli packed the jury with individuals who love guns and “conceal and carry” laws; Lizzie delivered one of the clearest and most persuasive opening statements I’ve ever heard; Lizzie and Eli prevailed on their motion for a partial directed verdict; the judge, relying on a terrific bench memo that Eli drafted, accepted our jury instructions and therefore accurately summarized the law on waiver; and Lizzie did not kill opposing counsel when, during his closing argument, he violated an order in limine by arguing that there's a tremendous need for public housing and HACC should be allowed to give Mr. Kdd's unit to someone more deserving, and he intentionally misstated the law on waiver as set forth in the jury instructions.</font></font></font></p><p><font color=\"#000000\" face=\"Times New Roman\" size=\"3\"></font><font face=\"Times New Roman\"><font size=\"3\"><font color=\"#000000\">Last night at 9&#58;30, an exhausted and previously deadlocked jury emerged from their deliberations to rule in favor of Mr. Kidd, who responded by belting out the Queen classic, “We Are The Champions.”<span>&#160; </span></font></font><font size=\"3\"><font color=\"#000000\">HACC will not likely appeal, which means we won’t have to defend the trial court’s decision by joining forces with the NRA, which would love to challenge HACC’s blanket ban against guns.</font></font></font></p></div>",
