        "Title": "Reisman Missive Nets Senior $3300",
        "Body": "<div class=\"ExternalClassC2D1EB9B1F164B909C8631E3AFA0888F\"><p>Jamie’s senior client got bilked by a repairman who charged her $5,800 to install a leaky boiler.  He wouldn’t fix it, so Jamie helped client file a letter complaint with the Chicago Department of Business Affairs and Consumer Protection.  City filed an administrative action against the repairman who pled guilty to one count of consumer fraud.  City ordered restitution in the amount of $3,300 (and client got someone else to fix the boiler).</p><p>Client sent Jamie a copy of the administrative order and the $3,300 check she received and included a note that said, “God bless you, Ms. Reisman.  I cannot THANK you enough.”  (emphasis in original)<br></p></div>",
